# Notification Handlers Directory

Place your concrete notification handler implementations here.

## Example Structure

```php
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace App\Services\Notifications\Handlers;

use App\Enums\Notification\NotificationType;
use App\Models\User;
use App\Services\Notifications\AbstractNotificationHandler;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Mail;

class ExampleNotificationHandler extends AbstractNotificationHandler
{
    public function getNotificationType(): NotificationType
    {
        return NotificationType::EXAMPLE_TYPE;
    }

    protected function validate(User $receiver, array $parameters): void
    {
        parent::validate($receiver, $parameters);

        // Add custom validation here
        // Example: Check for required parameters
        if (!isset($parameters['example_field'])) {
            throw new \InvalidArgumentException('Missing required parameter: example_field');
        }
    }

    protected function send(User $receiver, array $parameters): bool
    {
        // Implement your notification sending logic here
        // Example: Send email, SMS, push notification, etc.

        try {
            // Your implementation
            // Example: Mail::to($receiver->email)->send(new ExampleMailable($parameters));

            return true;
        } catch (\Exception $e) {
            return false;
        }
    }
}
```

## Usage

1. Create your notification type in `App\Enums\Notification\NotificationType`
2. Create your handler class extending `AbstractNotificationHandler`
3. Implement `getNotificationType()` and `send()` methods
4. Register the handler in `NotificationServiceProvider::boot()`

```php
// In NotificationServiceProvider::boot()
$registry->register($this->app->make(ExampleNotificationHandler::class));
```

5. Use the service to send notifications:

```php
$notificationService->send(
    $user,
    NotificationType::EXAMPLE_TYPE,
    ['example_field' => 'value']
);
```
